<script data-name="featured-video-mapped-to-wiki">
(function () {
// we can't use mw.config here because it's too early so we need to pass this data in different way
const videoDetails = {
mapping: {"mediaId":"CR0MZ2ZP","connatixPlaylistId":"fa733fa7-0131-48d3-a444-611bc76031fe","impressionsPerSession":3,"isDefaultMapping":true},
impressionsPerSession: 3,
};
const videoBridgeCountries = ["AE","AG","AL","AM","AR","AT","AU","AZ","BA","BB","BD","BG","BH","BN","BO","BR","BS","BY","CA","CH","CL","CN","CO","CR","CU","CY","CZ","DE","DK","DO","DZ","EC","EE","EG","ES","FI","FR","GB","GE","GF","GG","GH","GP","GR","GT","GU","GY","HK","HN","HR","HU","ID","IE","IL","IM","IN","IQ","IR","IS","IT","JE","JM","JO","JP","KE","KG","KH","KR","KW","KY","KZ","LA","LB","LK","LT","LU","LV","LY","MA","MD","ME","MK","MM","MN","MO","MQ","MT","MU","MV","MX","MY","NG","NI","NL","NO","NP","NZ","OM","PA","PE","PH","PK","PL","PR","PS","PT","PY","QA","RE","RO","RS","RU","SA","SC","SE","SG","SI","SK","SV","TD","TH","TN","TR","TT","TW","UA","US","UY","UZ","VE","VI","VN","ZA","ZW"];
const tier3VideoBridgeCountries = ["GB","BE","NL","DE","AU","MX","AR","FR","MD","CA","ES","IE","IT","PE","CO","CL","NZ"];
let hasVideoOnPage = null;

function getCookieValue(cookieName) {
const cookieSplit = ('; ' + document.cookie).split('; ' + cookieName + '=');
return cookieSplit.length === 2 ? cookieSplit.pop().split(';').shift() : null;
}

function hasMaxedOutPlayerImpressionsInWiki() {
const impressionsSoFar = Number(getCookieValue('playerImpressionsInWiki')) || 0;
const allowedImpressions = Number(videoDetails.impressionsPerSession);

return impressionsSoFar >= allowedImpressions;
}

function getCountryCode() {
try {
return JSON.parse(decodeURIComponent(getCookieValue('Geo'))).country.toLowerCase();
} catch {
return null;
}
}

function isVideoBridgeAllowedForCountry() {
const countryCode = getCountryCode();

if (!countryCode) {
return false;
}

// If it's a default mapping, then check the country whitelist from the default mapping.
if (videoDetails?.mapping?.isDefaultMapping) {
// If the wiki is classified as a tier3 wiki, then check the country whitelist from the tier3VideoBridge whitelist.
const allowedCountriesForTier3Wikis = tier3VideoBridgeCountries.map(function (allowedTier3CountryCode) {
return allowedTier3CountryCode.toLowerCase();
})

return allowedCountriesForTier3Wikis.indexOf(countryCode) !== -1;
} else {
// If not a default mapping wiki (so it's a wiki mapping), then check the country whitelist from the videoBridge whitelist
const allowedCountries = videoBridgeCountries.map(function (allowedCountryCode) {
return allowedCountryCode.toLowerCase();
});

return allowedCountries.indexOf(countryCode) !== -1;
}
}

window.fandomIsVideoPossible = function () {
if (hasVideoOnPage === null) {
hasVideoOnPage =
videoDetails.mapping &&
isVideoBridgeAllowedForCountry() &&
!hasMaxedOutPlayerImpressionsInWiki();
}

return hasVideoOnPage;
};

window.canPlayVideo = function () {
return window.fandomIsVideoPossible()
};

if (!window.canPlayVideo()) {
document.body.classList.add('no-featured-video');
} else {
document.body.classList.add('has-featured-video');
}
})();
</script>

<p><b>Exploration</b> is a mechanic introduced in the <a href="/wiki/Prophecy_of_Kings" title="Prophecy of Kings">Prophecy of Kings</a> Expansion for Twilight Imperium Fourth Edition and enables players to gain further rewards for expanding and reaching new systems.
</p><p>For a breakdown of Exploration Cards visit <a href="/wiki/Analysis_of_Exploration_Cards" title="Analysis of Exploration Cards">Analysis of Exploration Cards</a>.
</p>

<ul>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Exploring_Planets">Exploring Planets</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: Exploring Planets" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-label="edit-section-anon" data-action="edit-section" href="https://twilight-imperium.fandom.com/wiki/Exploration?veaction=edit&amp;section=1" aria-label="Edit section: Exploring Planets"><svg class="wds-icon wds-icon-tiny" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><use xlink:href="#wds-icons-pencil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>When a player <a href="/wiki/Invasion" title="Invasion">takes control</a> of a planet that is not already controlled by another player, they explore that planet.
</p><p>Exploring a planet involves drawing 1 card from the Exploration Deck corresponding to that planet's <a href="/wiki/Planets_and_Systems#Planet_Traits" class="mw-redirect" title="Planets and Systems">trait</a> (Hazardous, Industrial, or Cultural) and immediately resolving that card's effect. The card is then discarded unless it is a Relic Fragment, has an <a href="/wiki/Attach" class="mw-redirect" title="Attach">ATTACH</a> ability, or specifically instructs that it be placed in the play area.
</p>
<ul><li>A planet with no trait <u>cannot</u> be explored</li></ul>
<ul><li>If a player gains control of multiple planets at the same time, they choose the order in which they explore those planets, drawing and resolving each planet’s exploration card before exploring the next planet.</li></ul>
<ul><li>A planet that has been explored may be explored again through the use of the Technology <a href="/wiki/Cybernetic_Technologies#Scanlink_Drone_Network" title="Cybernetic Technologies">Scanlink Drone Network</a> or other abilities.</li></ul>
<p><br />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Exploring_Frontier_Tokens">Exploring Frontier Tokens</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: Exploring Frontier Tokens" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-label="edit-section-anon" data-action="edit-section" href="https://twilight-imperium.fandom.com/wiki/Exploration?veaction=edit&amp;section=2" aria-label="Edit section: Exploring Frontier Tokens"><svg class="wds-icon wds-icon-tiny" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><use xlink:href="#wds-icons-pencil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<figure class="thumb " typeof="mw:File/Thumb" style="width: 66px"> <a href="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/0/0d/FrontierToken.png/revision/latest?cb=20201107034355" class="mw-file-description image"><img alt="FrontierToken" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="66" height="64" class="thumbimage lazyload" data-image-name="FrontierToken.png" data-image-key="FrontierToken.png" data-relevant="0" data-src="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/0/0d/FrontierToken.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/66?cb=20201107034355" /></a> <noscript><a href="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/0/0d/FrontierToken.png/revision/latest?cb=20201107034355" class="mw-file-description image"><img alt="FrontierToken" src="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/0/0d/FrontierToken.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/66?cb=20201107034355" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="66" height="64" class="thumbimage" data-image-name="FrontierToken.png" data-image-key="FrontierToken.png" data-relevant="0" data-src="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/0/0d/FrontierToken.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/66?cb=20201107034355" /></a></noscript> <figcaption class="thumbcaption"> </figcaption> </figure>
<p>During game setup, frontier tokens are placed on all systems that do not contain planets (e.g. Planetless Anomalies, Wormholes and Empty Space).
</p>
<ul><li>A frontier token is placed in the <a href="/wiki/Planets_and_Systems#Wormholes" class="mw-redirect" title="Planets and Systems">Creuss Gate</a> System</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Planets_and_Systems#Hyperlane_Tiles" class="mw-redirect" title="Planets and Systems">Hyperlane</a> tiles do not count as systems</li></ul>
<p>If a player has the technology <a href="/wiki/Propulsion_Technologies#Dark_Energy_Tap" title="Propulsion Technologies">Dark Energy Tap</a>, after they perform a <a href="/wiki/Tactical_Action" title="Tactical Action">tactical action</a> in a system that contains a frontier token, if they have 1 or more ships in that system, they may explore that token.
</p><p>In some cases, an ability may instruct a player to explore a frontier token. In those cases, they may do so even if they do not own the Dark Energy Tap technology.
</p><p>Exploring a planetless system involves drawing a card from the Frontier Deck.
</p><p>After a frontier token is explored, it is discarded and returned to the supply.<br />
</p><p><br />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="List_of_Exploration_and_Frontier_Cards">List of Exploration and Frontier Cards</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: List of Exploration and Frontier Cards" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-label="edit-section-anon" data-action="edit-section" href="https://twilight-imperium.fandom.com/wiki/Exploration?veaction=edit&amp;section=3" aria-label="Edit section: List of Exploration and Frontier Cards"><svg class="wds-icon wds-icon-tiny" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><use xlink:href="#wds-icons-pencil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<figure class="thumb show-info-icon" typeof="mw:File/Thumb" style="width: 300px"> <a href="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/9/96/Ti10_explorationbacks_composite.png/revision/latest?cb=20200811060949" class="mw-file-description image"><img alt="Ti10 explorationbacks composite" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="300" height="151" class="thumbimage lazyload" data-image-name="Ti10 explorationbacks composite.png" data-image-key="Ti10_explorationbacks_composite.png" data-relevant="1" data-src="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/9/96/Ti10_explorationbacks_composite.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/300?cb=20200811060949" /></a> <noscript><a href="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/9/96/Ti10_explorationbacks_composite.png/revision/latest?cb=20200811060949" class="mw-file-description image"><img alt="Ti10 explorationbacks composite" src="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/9/96/Ti10_explorationbacks_composite.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/300?cb=20200811060949" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="300" height="151" class="thumbimage" data-image-name="Ti10 explorationbacks composite.png" data-image-key="Ti10_explorationbacks_composite.png" data-relevant="1" data-src="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/9/96/Ti10_explorationbacks_composite.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/300?cb=20200811060949" /></a></noscript> <figcaption class="thumbcaption"> <a href="/wiki/File:Ti10_explorationbacks_composite.png" class="info-icon"><svg><use xlink:href="#wds-icons-info-small"></use></svg></a> </figcaption> </figure><p>There are a total of 60 exploration cards (20 Cultural, 20 Industrial, 20 Hazardous), and 20 frontier cards.
</p><p>Each deck is identified by the corresponding symbol on its back (shown in the image).
</p><p><br />
</p>

</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Frontier_Cards">Frontier Cards</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: Frontier Cards" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-label="edit-section-anon" data-action="edit-section" href="https://twilight-imperium.fandom.com/wiki/Exploration?veaction=edit&amp;section=7" aria-label="Edit section: Frontier Cards"><svg class="wds-icon wds-icon-tiny" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><use xlink:href="#wds-icons-pencil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>

</p><h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Relic_Fragments">Relic Fragments</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: Relic Fragments" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-label="edit-section-anon" data-action="edit-section" href="https://twilight-imperium.fandom.com/wiki/Exploration?veaction=edit&amp;section=10" aria-label="Edit section: Relic Fragments"><svg class="wds-icon wds-icon-tiny" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><use xlink:href="#wds-icons-pencil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<figure class="mw-halign-right" typeof="mw:File"><a href="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/c/c8/RelicDeck2.png/revision/latest?cb=20211015064609" class="mw-file-description image"><img alt="RelicDeck2" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="120" height="180" class="mw-file-element lazyload" data-image-name="RelicDeck2.png" data-image-key="RelicDeck2.png" data-relevant="1" data-src="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/c/c8/RelicDeck2.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/120?cb=20211015064609" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure><p class="_1qeIAgB0cPwnLhDF9XSiJM">Some exploration and frontier cards are relic fragments. Relic Fragments are divided into 3 types: industrial, hazardous, and cultural - corresponding to the <a href="/wiki/Planets_and_Systems#Planet_Traits" class="mw-redirect" title="Planets and Systems">planet trait</a> where they were explored.</p><p class="_1qeIAgB0cPwnLhDF9XSiJM">Relic Fragments drawn from the Frontier Deck are called 'Unknown Relic Fragments' and can act as any type as needed.</p><p class="_1qeIAgB0cPwnLhDF9XSiJM">When a player draws a relic fragment, they place it face up in their play area. </p><p class="_1qeIAgB0cPwnLhDF9XSiJM">If a player has 3 Relic Fragments of the <u>same</u> type, they may take an action to <a href="/wiki/Purge" title="Purge">purge</a> them and gain 1 relic (i.e. draw 1 Relic Card from the Relic Deck). Relic Fragments can be traded to other players as part of a <a href="/wiki/Transactions_%26_Deals" title="Transactions &amp; Deals">transaction</a>.
</p><h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Relics"><a href="/wiki/Relics" title="Relics">Relics</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: Relics" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-label="edit-section-anon" data-action="edit-section" href="https://twilight-imperium.fandom.com/wiki/Exploration?veaction=edit&amp;section=11" aria-label="Edit section: Relics"><svg class="wds-icon wds-icon-tiny" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><use xlink:href="#wds-icons-pencil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Relics have a wide variety of powerful abilities; some are single use, others grant passive abilities, and a select few reward victory points (with conditions).
</p><p>Relics <u>cannot</u> be traded.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Prophecy_of_Kings"><a href="/wiki/Prophecy_of_Kings" title="Prophecy of Kings">Prophecy of Kings</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: Prophecy of Kings" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-label="edit-section-anon" data-action="edit-section" href="https://twilight-imperium.fandom.com/wiki/Exploration?veaction=edit&amp;section=12" aria-label="Edit section: Prophecy of Kings"><svg class="wds-icon wds-icon-tiny" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><use xlink:href="#wds-icons-pencil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>These 10 Relics were introduced in the <a href="/wiki/Prophecy_of_Kings" title="Prophecy of Kings">Prophecy of Kings</a> expansion
</p>
<table class="article-table">
<tbody><tr>
<th><b>Name</b>
</th>
<th><b>Effect</b>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>Dominus Orb
</td>
<td>Before you move units during a <a href="/wiki/Tactical_Action" title="Tactical Action">tactical action</a>, you may <a href="/wiki/Purge" title="Purge">purge</a> this card to <a href="/wiki/Movement" title="Movement">move</a> and <a href="/wiki/Movement#Transport" title="Movement">transport</a> units that are in systems that contain 1 of your <a href="/wiki/Command_Tokens" title="Command Tokens">command tokens</a>.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Maw of Worlds
</td>
<td>At the start of the <a href="/wiki/Agenda_Phase" title="Agenda Phase">agenda phase</a>, you may <a href="/wiki/Purge" title="Purge">purge</a> this card and <a href="/wiki/Readied_and_Exhausted" title="Readied and Exhausted">exhaust</a> all of your planets to gain any 1 <a href="/wiki/Technology" title="Technology">technology</a>.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Scepter of Emelpar
</td>
<td>When you would spend a <a href="/wiki/Command_Tokens" title="Command Tokens">token</a> from your <a href="/wiki/Command_Sheet" title="Command Sheet">strategy pool</a>, you may <a href="/wiki/Readied_and_Exhausted" title="Readied and Exhausted">exhaust</a> this card to spend a token from your <a href="/wiki/Reinforcements" title="Reinforcements">reinforcements</a> instead.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Shard of the Throne
</td>
<td>When you gain this card, gain 1 victory point. When you lose this card, lose 1 victory point.
<p>When a player <a href="/wiki/Invasion" title="Invasion">gains control</a> of a <a href="/wiki/Planets_and_Systems#Legendary_Planets" class="mw-redirect" title="Planets and Systems">legendary planet</a> you control, or a planet you control in your <a href="/wiki/Home_System" class="mw-redirect" title="Home System">home system</a>, that player gains this card.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Stellar Converter
</td>
<td>ACTION: Choose 1 non-<a href="/wiki/Home_System" class="mw-redirect" title="Home System">home</a>, non-<a href="/wiki/Planets_and_Systems#Legendary_Planets" class="mw-redirect" title="Planets and Systems">legendary planet</a> other than Mecatol Rex in a system that is <a href="/wiki/Planets_and_Systems#Adjacency" class="mw-redirect" title="Planets and Systems">adjacent</a> to 1 or more of your units that have <a href="/wiki/Bombardment" title="Bombardment">BOMBARDMENT</a>; destroy all units on that planet and <a href="/wiki/Purge" title="Purge">purge</a> its attachments and its planet card. Then, place the destroyed planet token on that planet and purge this card.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>The Codex
</td>
<td>ACTION: <a href="/wiki/Purge" title="Purge">Purge</a> this card to take up to 3 <a href="/wiki/Action_Cards" title="Action Cards">action cards</a> of your choice from the action card discard pile.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>The Crown of Emphidia
</td>
<td>After you perform a <a href="/wiki/Tactical_Action" title="Tactical Action">tactical action</a>, you may <a href="/wiki/Readied_and_Exhausted" title="Readied and Exhausted">exhaust</a> this card to explore 1 planet you control
<p>At the end of the <a href="/wiki/Status_Phase" title="Status Phase">status phase</a>, if you control the "Tomb of Emphidia" <span typeof="mw:File"><a href="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/9/9c/CrownSymbol.png/revision/latest?cb=20201107044250" class="mw-file-description image"><img alt="CrownSymbol" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="20" height="21" class="mw-file-element lazyload" data-image-name="CrownSymbol.png" data-image-key="CrownSymbol.png" data-relevant="0" data-src="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/twilight-imperium-4/images/9/9c/CrownSymbol.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20201107044250" /></a></span>, you may <a href="/wiki/Purge" title="Purge">purge</a> this card to gain 1 Victory Point.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>The Crown of Thalnos
</td>
<td>During each <a href="/wiki/Combat" title="Combat">combat</a> round, this card's owner may reroll any number of their dice, applying +1 to the results; any units that reroll dice but do not produce at least 1 hit are destroyed.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>The Obsidian
</td>
<td>When you gain this card, draw 1 <a href="/wiki/Objectives#Secret_Objectives" title="Objectives">secret objective</a>. You can have 1 additional scored or unscored secret objective.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>The Prophet's Tears
</td>
<td>When you research a <a href="/wiki/Technology" title="Technology">technology</a>, you may <a href="/wiki/Readied_and_Exhausted" title="Readied and Exhausted">exhaust</a> this card to ignore 1 prerequisite or draw 1 <a href="/wiki/Action_Cards" title="Action Cards">action card</a>.
</td></tr></tbody></table>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Codex_IV"><a href="/wiki/Codex_I_-_IV_(Fourth_Edition_Expansion)#Volume_IV_(Liberation)" title="Codex I - IV (Fourth Edition Expansion)">Codex IV</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: Codex IV" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-label="edit-section-anon" data-action="edit-section" href="https://twilight-imperium.fandom.com/wiki/Exploration?veaction=edit&amp;section=14" aria-label="Edit section: Codex IV"><svg class="wds-icon wds-icon-tiny" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><use xlink:href="#wds-icons-pencil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>

</p>

<th><b>Name</b>

</td>
<td>Your units do not roll for <a href="/wiki/Planets_and_Systems#Gravity_Rift" class="mw-redirect" title="Planets and Systems">gravity rifts</a>, and you ignore the movement effects of other <a href="/wiki/Planets_and_Systems#Anomalies" class="mw-redirect" title="Planets and Systems">anomalies</a>.
<p>ACTION: Exhaust this card to explore a frontier token in a system that does not contain any other players' ships.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Book of Latvinia
</td>
<td>When you gain this card, research up to 2 technologies that have no prerequisites.
<p>ACTION: Purge this card; if you control planets that have all 4 types of <a href="/wiki/Technology#Technology_Specialty_Planets" title="Technology">technology specialties</a>, gain 1 victory point. Otherwise, gain the speaker token.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Neuraloop
</td>
<td>When a public objective is revealed, you may purge one of your <a class="mw-selflink-fragment" href="#Relic_Fragments_and_Relics">relics</a> to discard that objective and replace it with a random objective from any objective deck; that objective is a public objective, even if it is a secret objective.
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<h3><span id="Thunder.27s_Edge"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Thunder's_Edge"><a href="/wiki/Thunder%27s_Edge" title="Thunder&#39;s Edge">Thunder's Edge</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title="Edit section: Thunder&#039;s Edge" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-label="edit-section-anon" data-action="edit-section" href="https://twilight-imperium.fandom.com/wiki/Exploration?veaction=edit&amp;section=15" aria-label="Edit section: Thunder&#039;s Edge"><svg class="wds-icon wds-icon-tiny" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><use xlink:href="#wds-icons-pencil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>These 7 Relics were introduced in the Thunder's Edge expansion.
</p>
<table class="article-table">
<tbody><tr>
<th><b>Name</b>
</th>
<th><b>Effect</b>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>Metali Void Armaments
</td>
<td>During the "Anti Fighter Barrage" step of space combat, you may resolve ANTI-FIGHTER BARRAGE 6 (X3) against your opponent's units.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>The Quantumcore
</td>
<td>When you gain this card, gain your breakthrough.
<p>You have SYNERGY for all technology types.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>The Silver Flame
</td>
<td>The Silver Flame may be exchanged as part of a transaction.
<p>ACTION: Roll 1 die and purge this card; if the result is a 10, gain 1 victory point. Otherwise, purge your home system and all units in it; you cannot score public objectives. Put the Fracture into play if it is not already.
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Lightrail Ordnance
</td>
<td>Your space docks gain SPACE CANNON 5 (X2). You may use your space dock's SPACE CANNON against ships that are adjacent to their system.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Metali Void Shielding
</td>
<td>Each time hits are produced against 1 of your non-fighter ships, 1 of those ships may use SUSTAIN DAMAGE as if it had that ability.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>The Triad
</td>
<td>This card can be readied and spent as if it were a planet card. Its resource and influence values are equal to 3 plus the number of different types of relic fragments you own.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Heart of Ixth
</td>
<td>After any die is rolled, you may exhaust this card to add or subtract 1 from its results.
</td></tr></tbody></table>
